reviews.review_text:
This Is An Audience Recording? If it is, it is straight-on perfection.

Excellent sound and soul well-captured the peak of racing horses.

Too enthusiastically enjoying this show to render an unbiased opinion.

I'll try to do better next time.
Bruce Hornsby's first show with the Grateful Dead Good show, only post Brent gimme some lovin. It's not the same without his B-3 and soulfulness.

Good show good recording Really crisp audience tape.  Jerry's voice is a bit weathered, but he soldiers through.  Box of Rain, The Weight, and Bruce Hornsby sings Gimme Some Lovin'..  All at the Garden.
